# SESSION PROTOCOL

---

## ENTER SESSION CHECKLIST

Run this at the start of every new conversation before doing any work.

Quick trigger phrase Ryan can use:
"Run entry checklist + weekly tracker sync."
When this is requested, run the full entry checklist including 4b and (if Saturday) 4c/4d.

Automatic trigger rule:
- If Ryan starts a new chat with a message that implies session start (examples: "new session", "start session", "let's begin", "what should we work on today", "run the checklist"), run the full Enter Session Checklist automatically before other work.
- Do not wait for exact wording.
- Exception: if Ryan clearly says this is a quick one-off question, follow the "WHEN TO SKIP THE ENTRY BRIEFING" rules.

1. **Check the time**
   Run: `powershell -Command "Get-Date -Format 'dddd, MMMM dd yyyy h:mm tt'"`
   Report the time to Ryan and state peak vs. off-peak status.

2. **Pull latest from GitHub**
   Run: `cd "c:\App Development\sticker-quest"; git pull origin main`
   If there are conflicts or errors, report them to Ryan before proceeding.
   If already up to date, note it briefly and move on.

3. **Read PROJECT_CONTEXT.md**
   Confirm current phase, open flags, and any decisions that affect today's work.

4. **Read the last 2 entries in PATCH_NOTES.md**
   Know what was done in the last session and what was left unfinished.

4a. **Amber notes triage (when Amber docs exist)**
   Review Amber-related notes before planning work:
   - `docs/TONIGHT_AMBER_TEST_RESULTS.md`
   - `docs/AMBER_TEST_HISTORY.md`
   - `docs/NEXT_TASK_TEST_GATE.md`
   Classify Amber follow-ups into:
   - **Do now (this session)**
   - **Schedule next session**
   - **Save for later backlog**
   Surface the top Amber priority in the 3-line briefing so it is not missed.

4b. **Weekly tracker sync (always)**
   Open `docs/WEEKLY_EXECUTION_TRACKER.md` and confirm:
   - Current week block exists
   - Today's day theme is defined
   - Planned hours for today are set
   If missing, set them before starting work.

4b.1 **Daily schedule sync with prior exit (always)**
   Before proposing today's work, sync against the previous session's exit plan:
   - Read the last "Tomorrow Schedule + Carry-Forward" note in `PATCH_NOTES.md`
   - Confirm today's planned task from that note
   - Confirm unfinished items that carried forward
   - Confirm whether prior session worked ahead, on-plan, or behind
   Then report a "Today Schedule Snapshot" to Ryan:
   - **Scheduled today:** primary task for this day
   - **Carry-forward:** unfinished item(s) from prior session
   - **Work-ahead status:** worked ahead / on-plan / catch-up needed
   - **Sync tasks:** any quick admin/log updates that must be done first

4c. **Saturday audit trigger**
   If today is Saturday:
   - Run weekly quick audit first (before deep task work)
   - Produce Green/Yellow/Red verdict and top 2 corrective actions
   - Lock next week's must-ship item and day themes in the tracker

4d. **Saturday review runbook (30 minutes, repeatable)**
   Use this sequence every Saturday:
   1. Review planned vs actual hours and finish rate
   2. Score 6 habit signals (0/1/2) and compute weekly risk
   3. Set Green/Yellow/Red verdict + timeline impact
   4. Define top 2 corrective actions for next week
   5. Lock next week's must-ship item + daily themes
   6. Decide optional Saturday flex mode after planning: catch-up, work-ahead, or rest
   7. Confirm family-time priority before doing any optional Saturday work

4d.1 **Saturday — Lore Bible sprint surface**
   If today is Saturday: Surface the **Inkborne Lore Bible** sprint as the top off-peak design task. Target: run this week when possible. Say: "Lore Bible sprint is ready — ~30–45 min on claude.ai with Opus. See `docs/LORE_BIBLE_SPRINT_READY.md`. Want to run it today or slot it for later this week?" Include in the 3-line briefing or next-options.

4e. **Cursor model doc refresh (when billing reset)**
   Open `docs/CURSOR_MODEL_AND_MODE_REFERENCE.md` and check the **Billing cycle reset date**.
   If **today's date matches or has passed** that date: refresh the Usage status table (mark all models usable, clear exhausted notes), update the **Next reset** field with the new cycle date from the [Cursor dashboard](https://cursor.com/dashboard/usage), and note the refresh in `PATCH_NOTES.md`.
   If the reset date is blank, skip — Ryan will fill it when known.

5. **Surface the top open Known Flag**
   Check the "Known Flags" section of PROJECT_CONTEXT.md. Name the single most
   urgent unresolved issue so Ryan stays aware of it — even if we're not fixing it today.

6. **Check .env has real values (if code work is planned)**
   If the session involves Supabase features, verify EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and
   EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in .env are not placeholder strings.
   If blank: warn Ryan that Star Mail and any backend features will silently fail.

7. **Give Ryan a 3-line briefing:**
   - "Current phase: [X]. Last session: [what was done]."
   - "Open items: [top 1-2 things that need to happen next]."
   - "Time status: [peak/off-peak and what that means today]."
   - "Today's schedule: [today's planned task + carry-forward + work-ahead status]."

8. **Ask what Ryan wants to work on** — do not assume and charge ahead.

9. **Confirm the session plan**
   After Ryan tells you what he wants to do, confirm it back in plain English before starting:

   "Got it. Here's the plan for today:
   1. [Task 1]
   2. [Task 2] (if applicable)
   3. [Task 3] (if applicable)
   Let me know if you want to change anything before we start."

   Keep it to 3 items max. If Ryan gives more than 3, flag the scope risk and suggest prioritizing.
   Do not start work until Ryan confirms or adjusts the plan.

10. **Code-doc sync (reminder)**
   Quick trigger phrase Ryan can use: **"Run code-doc sync."**
   At **session wrap-up**, if Ryan used that phrase **or** the session changed **architecture** (root routing, new routes, Zustand store shape, major folder moves, new third-party integrations):
   - Update `docs/CODEBASE_MAP.md` (affected sections + **Last verified** date)
   - Mention the map update in `PATCH_NOTES.md` when non-trivial  
   *(See also Exit checklist 2c.)*

