## INTERIM COMMIT (90-MINUTE RULE)

If a session has been running for 90+ minutes without a commit:
- Pause and do an interim commit: `git add .` → `git commit` → `git push`
- Label it clearly: "Checkpoint: [brief description of work in progress]"
- Tell Ryan: "Saving a checkpoint to GitHub — nothing is lost if we stop here."
- Continue the session after the commit.

This prevents losing more than 90 minutes of work if anything goes wrong.

---

## PHASE COMPLETION AUDIT (Run at the end of each phase — not on a timer)

When a phase (1, 2, 3, etc.) is declared complete, run a dead code audit:
1. List all files in the project
2. Flag any that have not been touched and appear unrelated to Sticker Quest
   (Expo boilerplate, old test screens, superseded files)
3. Show Ryan the list and ask for approval before deleting anything
4. Never delete without explicit "yes delete this" from Ryan
5. Log all deletions in PATCH_NOTES.md

Known candidates for Phase 1 audit:
- `app/(tabs)/explore.tsx` — Expo default explore tab, unused
- `app/(tabs)/stress-test.tsx` — early test screen, may be unused
- `components/hello-wave.tsx` — Expo boilerplate
- `components/parallax-scroll-view.tsx` — Expo boilerplate
- `components/external-link.tsx` — Expo boilerplate

Do NOT delete these now. Audit happens at Phase 1 completion.

---

## WHEN TO SKIP THE ENTRY BRIEFING

Skip the full briefing if:
- Ryan explicitly says "just answer this question" or "quick question"
- The conversation is clearly a single strategy question with no code work
- The session is a continuation within the same conversation thread

Still check the time if any Claude Pro recommendations will be made.
Still pull from GitHub at the start of any session involving code changes.
